    "body": "> Hi there, I managed to launch ipython at a host and tried to access the htmlnotebook using an android-tablet.\n\nGreat :-)\n\n> First of all the overall experience is charming, though some points could maybe be optimized for mobile devices (in future?).\n\nMoving to [bootstrap](twitter.github.com/bootstrap/) may help, I know they have some 'responsive' design allowing different css depending on device type.\n\nTake a look at https://github.com/ipython/ipython/pull/2127 , it should allow you to add custom button in the toolbar, so you might be able to add an `edit` button . https://github.com/ipython/ipython/pull/2333 could give you an idea of how to  have button on top of each cell. \n\nDevelopping for tablet is hard as not all of US have some. And there are a lot to do on classical plateform also.\n"
  },
